<name>AIR CONDITIONING</name>
<ttl id="1002K_S000R_7A818_T005M" variety="T005M">
<name>AIR CONDITIONING SWITCH (for Manual Air Conditioning System)</name>
<para id="RM0000012KA00SX" category="G" type-id="3001K" name-id="ACFUF-01" from="201202">
<name>INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM0000012KA00SX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM0000012KA00SX_01_0004" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00004EV00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT COOLER SWITCH</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E225798E01" width="2.775699831in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check the cooler switch resistance.</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Using an ohmmeter, measure the resistance and check the results in accordance with the values in the table below.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard Resistance</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.38in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="1.38in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="1.37in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>5 - 6</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Cooler Switch OFF</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>5 - 6</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Cooler Switch ON</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the result is not as specified, replace the cooler switch.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check the A/C indicator operation.</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Connect the positive (+) lead from the battery to terminal 6 and the negative (-) lead to terminal 4.</ptxt>
</s3>
<s3>
<ptxt>Push the cooler switch in and check that the indicator lights up.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Indicator lights up</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the result is not as specified, replace the cooler switch.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check the illumination operation.</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Connect the positive (+) lead from the battery to terminal 3 and the negative (-) lead to terminal 1 and check that the bulb illuminates.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Bulb illuminates</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the result is not as specified, replace the cooler switch.</ptxt>
<table>
<title>Text in Illustration</title>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="0.41in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.72in"/>
